00:06:22.020 --> 00:06:24.400
So that's all I'm going to do
for-- well, we could do a

00:06:24.400 --> 00:06:25.280
couple of other things too.

00:06:25.280 --> 00:06:27.150
We can also figure out how
high the ball went.

00:06:27.150 --> 00:06:29.920
And how high the ball went is
actually no different than the

00:06:29.920 --> 00:06:32.020
1-dimensional problem.

00:06:32.020 --> 00:06:34.370
We know that this is the
initial velocity

00:06:34.370 --> 00:06:36.050
in its upward direction.

00:06:36.050 --> 00:06:37.790
We know it goes to 0.

00:06:37.790 --> 00:06:40.810
So its average velocity in
the upward direction

00:06:40.810 --> 00:06:41.870
is going to be what?

00:06:41.870 --> 00:06:44.310
Its average velocity in the
upward direction is going to

00:06:44.310 --> 00:06:47.910
be this plus this
divided by 2.

00:06:47.910 --> 00:06:52.480
So the average horizontal
velocity--

00:06:52.480 --> 00:06:54.030
vertical velocity, sorry.

00:06:54.030 --> 00:06:57.090
Vertical velocity average.

00:06:57.090 --> 00:06:58.870
This is funny notation.

00:06:58.870 --> 00:07:00.030
Is just going to be
half of this.

00:07:00.030 --> 00:07:04.000
It's going to be 5 square
root of 2 over 2.

00:07:04.000 --> 00:07:07.230
And it travels that
for how long?

00:07:07.230 --> 00:07:09.420
Well just while it's going up,
it travels that for a square

00:07:09.420 --> 00:07:11.755
root of 2 seconds times the
square root of 2 seconds.

00:07:16.050 --> 00:07:18.660
Distance is the average
velocity times time.

00:07:18.660 --> 00:07:19.750
So this is a sequel.

00:07:19.750 --> 00:07:23.060
This square root of 2 times this
square root of 2 is 2,

00:07:23.060 --> 00:07:24.350
and it cancels out with this.

00:07:24.350 --> 00:07:29.290
So the peak height that we could
say, the height is going

00:07:29.290 --> 00:07:31.390
to be 5 meters.

00:07:31.390 --> 00:07:32.360
So that's pretty neat.

00:07:32.360 --> 00:07:35.500
If I throw something at 10
meters per second at a 45

00:07:35.500 --> 00:07:38.730
degree angle, its maximum height
is going to be 5 meters

00:07:38.730 --> 00:07:40.550
and it's going to
go 20 meters.

00:07:40.550 --> 00:07:43.050
So I could draw that.

00:07:43.050 --> 00:07:46.110
Image, clear image.

